    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hello @hacker-DOM \r\n\r\nSome contract are treated in a particular way, because it could be unsafe to have them not be the first one in the inheritance tree. This is, in particular, the case of `Initializable`.\r\n\r\nTo avoid any issue, we have an unwritten rule to ALWAYS inherit Context as the first child if `_msgSender` is used in the contract, regardless of weither it is indirectly inherited or not.",
